03/04/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia's opposition ethnic Albanian New Democracy (ND) party said on Saturday (April 2nd) it will take part in early parliamentary elections. 
ND leader Imer Selmani did not exclude possible coalition with other ethnic Albanian opposition parties during the election campaign. 
The snap elections are expected to be called for June on the proposition of the senior ruling VMRO-DPMNE as the main opposition SDSM dropped all demands and said it will participate in the elections. 
(Kanal 5, Alsat M, A1 - 02/04/11)
